    {
      "id": "course-2864bc1bad9e",
      "title": "REWRITE: Python for Vibe-Coders - Complete Course (NOT just code snippets)",
      "description": "CRITICAL: The current version is NOT a course - it's just code snippets with no teaching.\n\nA COMPLETE beginner course MUST include for EACH module:\n\n1. **Learning objectives** - What will the student be able to do after this module?\n2. **Prerequisites check** - What should they know before starting?\n3. **Concept explanations** - Actually TEACH the concepts in plain English BEFORE showing code\n4. **Step-by-step instructions** - Walk through the code line by line, explaining what each part does\n5. **Practice exercises** - Multiple exercises for students to try themselves (with solutions)\n6. **Common mistakes** - What errors will beginners make? How to fix them?\n7. **Mini-project** - A small project that uses the module's concepts\n8. **Self-assessment quiz** - Questions to check understanding (with answers)\n\nMODULE 0 MUST INCLUDE:\n- How to install Python (Windows, Mac, Linux)\n- Choosing and setting up an IDE (VS Code recommended, with step-by-step)\n- How to create and run a .py file\n- What the terminal/command line is\n- Your first \"Hello World\"\n- Basic syntax: variables, strings, numbers, print()\n\nEACH MODULE should be 2000-4000 words of actual teaching content, not just code dumps.\n\nThe AI Pair-Coding Loop mentioned in the intro should be DEMONSTRATED in every module.\n\nTarget: Actual beginners who have never coded before.",
      "status": "done",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-18T05:21:58.117180Z",
      "assignee": "shuri",
      "priority": "high",
      "notes": "Previous version was rejected - it was just code snippets with no teaching. This needs COMPLETE rewrite with actual educational content.\nTriaged 2026-03-18 06:00 ET: moving rewrite into execution. Sequence: (1) Bob technical validation, (2) Inspector pedagogy QA, (3) Chet final consolidation. Parent stays inprogress until QA + final release complete.",
      "startedAt": "2026-03-18T10:00:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "course-5f652d3172cc",
      "title": "EXPAND: Data Analytics with AI - Add actual teaching content + resources",
      "description": "The current version has good STRUCTURE but is missing actual CONTENT.\n\nWhat's needed:\n\n1. **Expand lesson content** - Each \"Lesson content\" section is just bullet points. Write out the actual lessons (1500-3000 words per module explaining concepts).\n\n2. **Create the templates** - The course references these but they don't exist:\n   - Problem Framing Worksheet (downloadable)\n   - Data Cleaning Log template\n   - Executive Brief Template\n   \n3. **Create sample datasets** - The course references datasets that don't exist:\n   - Messy creator dataset for cleaning exercises\n   - Customers + orders + sessions for SQL exercises\n   - Newsletter funnel data for spreadsheet exercises\n\n4. **Tool setup guides** - Step-by-step installation for:\n   - DB Browser for SQLite\n   - Jupyter notebooks\n   - Tableau Public or alternative\n\n5. **SQL syntax teaching** - Module 4 mentions SQL but never teaches it. Add actual SQL lessons.\n\n6. **Answer keys** - All assessments need answers/rubrics.\n\n7. **Worked examples** - Show complete worked examples for each exercise type.\n\nThe structure is good - just fill in the actual teaching content.",
      "status": "done",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-18T05:21:58.117180Z",
      "assignee": "shuri",
      "priority": "high",
      "notes": "Structure is solid, needs content expansion. Don't change the module organization - just add depth."
    },
