    {
      "id": "19cf422439115ywcs",
      "title": "Content Tracker MVP",
      "status": "done",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-15T20:53:32.177299",
      "description": "**Goal:** Build an app to help solo creators track digital content on their websites and keep it up to date.\n\n**Target Platforms:** WordPress + custom sites\n\n**Core Features (MVP):**\n1. **Content Inventory** — Crawl site or connect to CMS, list all pages/posts/assets, tag by type\n2. **Freshness Scoring** — Track last-updated dates, flag stale content (configurable threshold), priority queue\n3. **Health Checks** — Broken link detection, missing images/alt text, basic SEO (meta descriptions, titles)\n4. **Dashboard** — At-a-glance site health, upcoming reviews, stale vs. fresh content\n\n**Scope:**\n- Solo creators (no team/permissions for MVP)\n- Reporting only (no auto-fix in v1)\n- Later: add auto-fix functionality, team features, more platforms\n\n**From:** Kev (2026-03-15)",
      "assignee": "shuri",
      "completedAt": "2026-03-15T21:41:14.392328",
      "notes": "Content Tracker MVP fully complete. All sub-tasks done: research, backend (crawler, freshness scoring, health checks, REST API), frontend (dashboard, inventory view), QA review, creative polish."
    },
